Do the right thing



As leaders and professionals, we're constantly faced with tough decisions and challenging situations. It's easy to get caught up in the pressure to perform, to hit our numbers, and to succeed.

But here's the thing: success isn't just about achieving our goals. It's about how we achieve them.

When we prioritize doing the right thing - even when it's hard, even when it's unpopular - we build trust, we build credibility, and we build strong relationships.

If one of these tough decisions have been eating at you last year, take a stand and make it right it your life or business.

What's one area in your business or personal life where you can focus on doing the right thing?

Is it being more transparent with your customers?

Is it taking a stand on a tough issue?

Is it simply being kind and compassionate to those around you?

Whatever it is, I encourage you to take action.

Doing the right thing isn't always easy. But it's always worth it.

Jevon's Paradox and Its Significance to Nvidia:

NVIDIA's dominance is only going to be further reinforced by DeepSeek's arrival. How?

The principle that supports this is known as Jevon's Paradox. Jevon's Paradox states that as a resource becomes more efficient, the consumption of that resource amplifies. In this case, as AI model training becomes more efficient, AI model training will become more accessible and higher in demand.

Think of how many companies thought they wouldn't be able to train llms due to the sheer cost of them. DeepSeek is paving the way forward in showing they CAN do so, and they won't need the expensive compute resources to get to the result they want. They don't need to leverage OpenAI's models or third party open-source models as much. In the end, who benefits? Nvidia.
postsData.commentAdded: Exciting times for AI! Jevons Paradox truly underscores the growing accessibility of model training‚ÄîNvidia is poised to thrive! üöÄ
